reviewText: No actual fighting.  Horrendous acting.  Cheap sets.  Not even decent parody.

Aspires to appear like a reality TV show (it could be shown on TV as there is no swearing or anything suggestive to see, they might as well wear swim suits). The owner of the league is a female and her husband is a coach. They have hired on a new coach who is clueless.

Numerous interviews, features five 'matches' where the gals mince around, some have make-up to appear battered. None appear to sweat. Some appear to be fit, featuring firm tummies. Virtually unwatchable except to the most faithful of watchers. Pass on this.
